It is really a shame that everyone feels the need to "bump up the flavor" with this. The beauty of this dish is the subtle flavors. The nutty sweetness that comes through is incredible and would be totally masked by doubling the garlic or the sage. I made this as written except that I used walnuts instead of hazelnuts (just to save money) and browned the butter (a way to make the flavor sing even more), and I added an extra onion and caramelized it fully (which is part of the recipe, I don't know why people say they added caramelized onions). Make this as is, be sure to salt properly, and you will be richly rewarded.

