Wow! It was an excellent fall dish. I loved it. I have mixed feelings about readers providing suggestions on how to perfect dishes, but the readers advice on this recipe served it very, very well. Specifically: 1. Add more butternut squash and sage. Taste the filling before you assemble the lasagna and adjust accordingly. At the end of the day, more vegetables don't hurt anyone and adds more substance. 2. Add more cheese. I think that's good advice for any recipe. 3. More importantly, let the pan sit for at least 20 minutes after the baking is finished. What the dish looked like when it came out of the oven versus how easy it was to cut and serve was palpable. 4. Most importantly, enjoy! It was yummy!

