Rating: 4
OMFG THIS WAS AMAZING!!! After reading so many good reviews, and then actually making the recipe - I firmly believe those who did not enjoy this recipe likely did something wrong. To make this recipe the ULTIMATE, do the following: - Gently sautee the chopped hazelnuts in butter. They become softer and soooo good. - Roast the squash, don't cut it up and fry it. That is WAY too much work. If you roast (350 degrees) and cool you can spoon the flesh out like butter. I then mix the onion/spice/hazelnuts into the sqash and mash together. - Use traditional noodles, I used traditional noodles and cooked them first - Double up on the spices - Add a touch more cheese, especially if entertaining - Add a touch of nutmeg to the bechamel. Yummy! **NOTE: This lasagna might be very goopy - if you are impatient you will have a globby, but delicious, mess. Do wait 15-20 minutes.**LASTLY: If you can, do things ahead of time. Roast the sqash a day before, etc.

