I've made this several times now and most recently for the vegetarians at Thanksgiving and for a Christmas party. Both times it was definitely a hit. I found that roasting the squash cubes at 450F for 20-25 min. after tossing them in a tablespoon or so of olive oil is much simpler and really brings out the squash flavor. For the hazelnuts/filberts I just toss them with the skins after they have cooled a bit into the food processor to chop them to the desired consistency. Per earlier reviews I also used regular lasagne noodles. This has more steps than some recipes but wow is it worth it and since so many steps can be done ahead it works wonderfully for a party. I've had nothing but compliments on this recipe.

