Rating: 4
This lasagne is not only unique, but it's incredibly delicious! Yeah, it's a bit tedious, but nothing worth doing was ever easy. To anyone who's ever dissected a butternut squash, you know it's difficult. Leave plenty of time for this task. Though, I would never dream of using canned pumpkin/squash/whate ver as a substitute or even mashing it! Also allow time to remove the skins from the hazelnuts. I poured boiling water over them and rubbed as much skin off as I could before putting them in the oven. I used slightly less than the 1 cup nuts stated and still found it to be a bit too nutty. When making the sauce, I added a pinch of freshly ground nutmeg, about a 1/2 tsp of paprika, and a sprinkle of dried chili flakes for a kick. I also added some spinach (about 250g) to my fillings - boiled, drained, and pressed to avoid making the dish too watery. Some previous reviews stated that it was not salted enough, so I just salted to taste instead of using measurements. Also, instead of using pre-shredded mozzarella, I used torn pieces of a fresh ball of mozzarella. I think that separated the flavours out a little instead of having everything melt together. Next time I might try goats cheese as suggested by another reviewer. I will definitely make it again - a great recipe for dinner parties!

