Rating: 4
This was fantastic. I made the filling and sauce the day before, although I added the nuts right before baking so they wouldn't get soggy. I used pre-cubed squash from Trader Joe's and then cut it down to about 1/4 inch cubes. That way it easily got tender in the 15 minutes of sautéing (but kept some texture  I would NOT advocate mashing it, as the lasagna would be too smoothly uniform), although I did pop a lid over the skillet for a few minutes to help that along. I also added a pinch of nutmeg to the béchamel. In the future, the only change Id make would be to leave off the very top pasta layer  it really just doesnt soften up enough, as the sauce runs down into the nooks in the pan, and I had to take it off before serving. I made a half recipe in an 8x8 and it was plenty for 4 people with one serving left over.

