This was really delicious. I made it exactly according to the recipe except that I didn't use hazelnuts--a big change, I know, but read on. I had a bottle of hazelnut oil that I'd bought for another recipe and wanted to use some of that instead of spending more money. So I subbed 1 Tb of hazelnut oil for 1 Tb of butter when sauteeing the squash and also when making the roux. I also added about 1 cup of browned ground turkey (drizzled a bit of hazelnut oil on that too) to replace the 1 cup of nuts. Anyway it was fantastic, very autumny, not too sweet (I added a bit more salt and pepper than the recipe called for to combat any sweetness), and not actually too rich--there's a lot less cheese than in many lasagna recipes. It reheats very well. It would make a really good special-occasion main dish for vegetarians, and I'll definitely make it again for a weekend supper for just us.

