Rating: 3
I liked this recipe a lot because it is so different from other "fall" flavor combinations and so unique compared to other vegetarian lasagnas. Cubing all that squash was a ton of work, but otherwise the recipe was excellent for preparing in steps in advance. I made the sauce and filling and grated the cheeses all 1-2 days in advance, and then it was easy to assemble before my party, and then just pop in the oven as guests were arriving. Being refrigerated, it did need an extra 15 minutes in the oven though. Also, the sauce will soak down through the layers, so make sure there is enough to pour on the top layer as the final step - my top noodles were just a bit stiff. Otherwise, I think this is delicious and impressive. I don't see why it couldn't be made with frozen cooked squash. The cubes were pretty, but I mostly liked them for the color which frozen squash would have as well - that would save a lot of work. Finally, this was served as part of a buffet, and I liked it that way because the pieces could be smaller. In larger quantities, the sqaush would be very rich, but I will definitely serve this again to guests.

