Wow. I pretty much followed this recipe to a T, and my husband and I were very impressed. I was worried that the sauce wasn't getting thick enough, but finally I gave up and just poured it on. It came out perfectly. The final product looked beautiful and tasted even better. It made a LOT more than 4 servings -- the two of us have eaten it for 4 meals and still have some left in the freezer (note: it gets better every time we eat it). A bit of an effort (we had to shell the hazelnuts ourselves and I attacked the raw squash rather than sticking it in the microwave), but it's definitely worth making again if I take the necessary shortcuts.

