Rating: 4
I was attracted to this recipe because of the roasted hazelnuts, and also trying to use squash in new ways. This recipe was delicious... the subtle flavors of the butternut squash combine very nicely with the hazelnuts,sage and cheese -- very unusual and something I don't think you'd find on too many restaurant menus either. It took longer to prepare than I anticipated (especially peeling/cutting squash, which I did cut in half and microwave to soften before peeling and cutting into cubes). Next time, I'll do this step the day before, as well as the sauce (and any other shredding or veg prep), that way all there is to do when ready to bake is layer it in the pan. My husband loved the taste also and there was enough for several meals. To the reader looking for Buffalo Mozzarella, I've seen this product at Costo Wholesale(if you have those up there!)

