I'm now very tempted to try this recipe, thanks to all the reviewers, I appreciate the suggestions (add spinach, microwave the butternut squash and once softened, scoop out rather than peeling the hard raw squash, adjust the sage quantity to taste, add a bit of smoked mozarella, etc.) One thing I thought I'd throw out there: it's been my experience that the mozarella cheese available here is fairly tasteless. Yes, it melts, but that's about all. However, I have heard that the Buffalo mozarella you can buy in the Italian deli's in New Jersey is fantastic, so I'd really like to try that with this recipe. Anyone out there know where I can find this great Italian 'Buffalo mozarella' in Toronto? I'll travel as far as Little Italy or Woodbridge :D .... thanks!!

