Rating: 4
This lasagne "wowed" my husband and friends that came over for dinner last night. It was fairly easy to assemble as well. The only thing I recommend is to take your squash, cut in half lengthwise and microwave until somewhat tender-it is just easier to peel and dice that way as well as cuts down on the sautee time. I would also increase the cheese measurement a little bit. Make sure your herbs are fresh, it makes all the difference! I am going to make it again for a small get together on Christmas Eve for family! I loved it......If you want something different, go for it, it tastes like something off the special menu at your favorite restaurant!

